    <h1>Branch Protection Regimes</h1>

    <ul class="breadcrumb">
        <li><a href="index.html">Dashboard</a></li>
        <li>Branch Protection</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="meta">Every non-archived repository in <code>TestOrg</code>, grouped into an ordered,
        exhaustive regime (BPR0..BPR5) by branch-protection control combination — the bypassable-vs-gated
        distinction the coverage percentage hides. 1 repositories classified.</p>

    
    <section class="card tier-na">
        <h2>BPR0 &middot; Unmeasured (0)</h2>
        <p class="meta">Protection status could not be read (permission-denied, transient, or unknown).</p>
        
        <p class="meta">No repositories in this band.</p>
        
    </section>
    
    <section class="card tier-fail">
        <h2>BPR1 &middot; Unprotected (0)</h2>
        <p class="meta">No effective baseline protection: unprotected, or force-push/deletion integrity not held.</p>
        
        <p class="meta">No repositories in this band.</p>
        
    </section>
    
    <section class="card tier-warn">
        <h2>BPR2 &middot; Integrity Only (0)</h2>
        <p class="meta">Force-push and deletion blocked, but no PR/review gate.</p>
        
        <p class="meta">No repositories in this band.</p>
        
    </section>
    
    <section class="card tier-warn">
        <h2>BPR3 &middot; Reviewed, Bypassable (0)</h2>
        <p class="meta">PR and review required, integrity held, but a broad bypass actor can skip the gate.</p>
        
        <p class="meta">No repositories in this band.</p>
        
    </section>
    
    <section class="card tier-pass">
        <h2>BPR4 &middot; Reviewed, Gated (0)</h2>
        <p class="meta">PR and review required, integrity held, no bypass — but no required status checks.</p>
        
        <p class="meta">No repositories in this band.</p>
        
    </section>
    
    <section class="card tier-pass">
        <h2>BPR5 &middot; Hardened (1)</h2>
        <p class="meta">PR, review, integrity, and required status checks all held, with no broad bypass.</p>
        
        <div class="table-wrapper">
            <table class="data-table" data-sortable>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th scope="col" data-sort-type="text">Repository <span class="tooltip-trigger tooltip-trigger-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Repository name; links to it on GitHub when a URL is known.">ⓘ<span class="sr-only">Repository name; links to it on GitHub when a URL is known.</span></span></th>
                        <th scope="col" data-sort-type="text">Visibility <span class="tooltip-trigger tooltip-trigger-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="The repository&#39;s GitHub visibility: Public, Internal, or Private.">ⓘ<span class="sr-only">The repository&#39;s GitHub visibility: Public, Internal, or Private.</span></span></th>
                        <th scope="col" class="text-center" data-nosort>PR Required <span class="tooltip-trigger tooltip-trigger-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Whether pull requests are required before merging.">ⓘ<span class="sr-only">Whether pull requests are required before merging.</span></span></th>
                        <th scope="col" class="text-center" data-sort-type="numeric">Reviewers <span class="tooltip-trigger tooltip-trigger-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Minimum number of required approving reviews, or — when not configured.">ⓘ<span class="sr-only">Minimum number of required approving reviews, or — when not configured.</span></span></th>
                        <th scope="col" class="text-center" data-nosort>Status Checks <span class="tooltip-trigger tooltip-trigger-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Whether required status checks are configured.">ⓘ<span class="sr-only">Whether required status checks are configured.</span></span></th>
                        <th scope="col" class="text-center" data-nosort>Admin Equivalent <span class="tooltip-trigger tooltip-trigger-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Whether administrators are subject to the branch protection rules.">ⓘ<span class="sr-only">Whether administrators are subject to the branch protection rules.</span></span></th>
                        <th scope="col" class="text-center" data-nosort>Broad Bypass <span class="tooltip-trigger tooltip-trigger-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Whether a broad bypass actor (e.g. org admin) can skip the protection rules.">ⓘ<span class="sr-only">Whether a broad bypass actor (e.g. org admin) can skip the protection rules.</span></span></th>
                        <th scope="col" class="text-center" data-nosort>Force-Push Blocked <span class="tooltip-trigger tooltip-trigger-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Whether force pushes are blocked on the protected branch.">ⓘ<span class="sr-only">Whether force pushes are blocked on the protected branch.</span></span></th>
                        <th scope="col" class="text-center" data-nosort>Deletion Blocked <span class="tooltip-trigger tooltip-trigger-header" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Whether branch deletion is blocked on the protected branch.">ⓘ<span class="sr-only">Whether branch deletion is blocked on the protected branch.</span></span></th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    
                    <tr>
                        <td><a href="https://github.com/TestOrg/repo-1"
                                target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">repo-1</a></td>
                        <td>Public</td>
                        <td class="text-center"><span class="status-dot status-pass" title="yes"><span class="sr-only">yes</span></span></td>
                        <td class="text-center">1</td>
                        <td class="text-center"><span class="status-dot status-pass" title="yes"><span class="sr-only">yes</span></span></td>
                        <td class="text-center"><span class="status-dot status-pass" title="yes"><span class="sr-only">yes</span></span></td>
                        <td class="text-center"><span class="status-dot status-fail" title="no"><span class="sr-only">no</span></span></td>
                        <td class="text-center"><span class="status-dot status-pass" title="yes"><span class="sr-only">yes</span></span></td>
                        <td class="text-center"><span class="status-dot status-pass" title="yes"><span class="sr-only">yes</span></span></td>
                    </tr>
                    
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
        
    </section>
    

</body>

</html>
